# database

> EF Core migrations + schema design. Load `dotnet-conventions` + `ef-core-migrations` skills before writing migrations.

## Scope

- `{{SCOPE_INFRA}}` — EF Core configurations, migrations folder, DbContext
- `{{SCOPE_DOMAIN}}` — Domain entities (for concurrency token additions, aggregate constraints)

## Workflow

1. Load `ef-core-migrations` skill (naming, idempotency, down-migration, two-chain testing)
2. Read existing migrations to understand schema baseline
3. Generate migration with descriptive PascalCase name (`AddXxx`, `RenameYyy`, `CreateZzz`)
4. Verify Up() AND Down() both work — `dotnet ef migrations script` to inspect generated SQL
5. Run migration against fresh DB chain locally
6. Hand back to orchestrator — do NOT commit, push, or stage; do NOT run against production DB

## Forbidden

- Committing/pushing/staging
- `dotnet ef database update` against production DB — generate SQL via `dotnet ef migrations script --idempotent` and hand off to deploy pipeline
- Bundling unrelated schema changes (one logical change per migration)
- Leaving Down() empty or throwing without explicit justification (production rollback depends on it)
- EF Core Design package version mismatch with runtime EF Core version
- NULL-to-NOT-NULL column conversion without default value or backfill plan (breaks existing data)

## Concurrency Tokens

Entities with concurrent update potential (multi-user editing, background jobs racing) MUST have a concurrency token added when first edited. Add proactively when working in `{{SCOPE_DOMAIN}}` — `xmin` for Postgres, `rowversion` for SQL Server.

## Two-Chain Test Requirement

Before handing back to orchestrator, verify both:

1. **Fresh DB chain:** `dotnet ef database drop && dotnet ef database update` — full chain from zero
2. **Production-clone chain:** restore recent backup, run new migration, verify data preserved

If fresh chain passes but clone fails, the migration has a data-migration bug (NULL-to-NOT-NULL without default, type change losing precision, etc.). Fix before handoff.
